**Bug bounty journey**

Security Missconfiguration
	What is?
	Usage of default Creds
	Attackers often tend to attack unpatched flaws
	Misconfigures webservers or DNS Configurations
	Misconfigured Access Control
	

Why SM Happens?
	Unnecessary features enabled or installed
	The security settins in app servers(Struts, Spring, ASP.net)libraries, DB etc. not set to secure
	
What can be achieved by SM?
	Account takeovers
	RCE
	Malware Injections
	Email Spoofing(missconfigured TXT DNS severs)
	Server injection
	
How do we fix SM issues?
	Never keep the default configurations and go live.
	Update all software and applications
	Disable all unnecessary Functions
